1570
01:30:07,300 --> 01:30:09,865
And deservedly so.

1571
01:30:09,966 --> 01:30:13,466
She did some things that were terrible.

1572
01:30:13,565 --> 01:30:16,132
And-and, yes,

1573
01:30:16,233 --> 01:30:18,733
we have a right to be pissed off at her.

1574
01:30:18,832 --> 01:30:21,733
But, you know,

1575
01:30:21,832 --> 01:30:24,565
she wasn't the only one.

1576
01:30:24,666 --> 01:30:29,166
She's just the only one
we fantasized about.

1577
01:30:30,166 --> 01:30:34,600
(cheers and applause)

1578
01:30:39,365 --> 01:30:41,500
AUDIENCE: Four more years!

1579
01:30:41,600 --> 01:30:44,432
Four more years! Four more years!

1580
01:30:44,533 --> 01:30:46,932
NIXON: We have brought over
half a million men home,

1581
01:30:47,033 --> 01:30:48,932
and more will be coming home.

1582
01:30:49,033 --> 01:30:52,065
We have ended America's ground combat role.

1583
01:30:52,166 --> 01:30:54,733
No draftees are being sent to Vietnam.

1584
01:30:54,832 --> 01:30:57,733
We have reduced our casualties by 98%.

1585
01:30:57,832 --> 01:30:59,632
We've gone the extra mile.

1586
01:30:59,733 --> 01:31:02,432
In fact, we've gone tens
of thousands of miles

1587
01:31:02,533 --> 01:31:04,932
trying to seek a negotiated
settlement of the war.

1588
01:31:05,033 --> 01:31:06,699
(applause)

1589
01:31:06,800 --> 01:31:09,500
There are three things,
however, that we have not

1590
01:31:09,600 --> 01:31:11,632
and that we will not offer.

1591
01:31:11,733 --> 01:31:14,832
We will never abandon our prisoners of war.

1592
01:31:14,932 --> 01:31:16,332
(cheers and applause)

1593
01:31:22,199 --> 01:31:23,832
And, second,

1594
01:31:23,932 --> 01:31:27,500
we will not join our enemies

1595
01:31:27,600 --> 01:31:31,100
in imposing a communist
government on our ally,

1596
01:31:31,199 --> 01:31:33,533
the 17 million people of South Vietnam.

1597
01:31:33,632 --> 01:31:36,332
(cheers and applause)

1598
01:31:39,666 --> 01:31:41,565
And we will never stain the honor

1599
01:31:41,666 --> 01:31:43,733
of the United States of America.

1600
01:31:43,832 --> 01:31:45,765
(cheers)

1601
01:32:26,765 --> 01:32:29,865
NARRATOR: Back in Paris, Henry
Kissinger was determined

1602
01:32:29,966 --> 01:32:34,399
to hammer out a peace agreement
before Election Day.

1603
01:32:34,500 --> 01:32:37,765
Now Le Duc Tho made a key concession.

1604
01:32:37,865 --> 01:32:40,065
Hanoi no longer insisted

1605
01:32:40,166 --> 01:32:43,699
that President Thieu had to go.

1606
01:32:43,800 --> 01:32:46,533
JOHN NEGROPONTE: There was
somehow this compulsion

1607
01:32:46,632 --> 01:32:50,132
to come to some kind of an agreement.

1608
01:32:50,233 --> 01:32:53,132
I remember Le Duc Tho when he
produced the draft agreement

1609
01:32:53,233 --> 01:32:59,466
in October 8 of '72 to Kissinger, saying,

1610
01:32:59,565 --> 01:33:00,865
"You're in a hurry, aren't you?

1611
01:33:00,966 --> 01:33:02,865
You want to do this quickly."

1612
01:33:02,966 --> 01:33:06,533
And-and the response was, "Yes."

1613
01:33:06,632 --> 01:33:10,065
NARRATOR: The two sides
soon had a tentative deal,

1614
01:33:10,166 --> 01:33:12,065
a "cease-fire in place"

1615
01:33:12,166 --> 01:33:14,565
to be followed within 60 days

1616
01:33:14,666 --> 01:33:17,565
by a complete withdrawal of U.S. troops

1617
01:33:17,666 --> 01:33:21,166
and the return of all American POWs.

1618
01:33:21,265 --> 01:33:25,432
The United States stopped
bombing the North.

1619
01:33:25,533 --> 01:33:31,033
No one had told President
Thieu any of the terms.

1620
01:33:32,666 --> 01:33:36,365
The day before Kissinger was to
arrive in Saigon to brief him,

1621
01:33:36,466 --> 01:33:40,100
Thieu was handed a document
found in an enemy bunker

1622
01:33:40,199 --> 01:33:42,332
in Quang Tin Province.

1623
01:33:42,432 --> 01:33:46,765
It was entitled "General
Instructions for Cease-Fire."

1624
01:33:46,865 --> 01:33:51,533
It meant that communist cadres
in an isolated province

1625
01:33:51,632 --> 01:33:55,966
of his own country already
knew more about what Kissinger

1626
01:33:56,065 --> 01:34:01,000
and Le Duc Tho had agreed
to in Paris than he did.

1627
01:34:01,100 --> 01:34:04,432
NEGROPONTE: And imagine
being given an agreement

1628
01:34:04,533 --> 01:34:09,899
concerning the fate of
your own country and, uh,

1629
01:34:10,000 --> 01:34:11,666
being told that you really don't have

1630
01:34:11,765 --> 01:34:15,332
any input in the matter.

1631
01:34:15,432 --> 01:34:18,899
And, oh, by the way, we
didn't even yet have

1632
01:34:19,000 --> 01:34:20,800
the Vietnamese translation,

1633
01:34:20,899 --> 01:34:22,632
because that hadn't been completed.

1634
01:34:22,733 --> 01:34:26,199
And we gave him the English version.

1635
01:34:26,300 --> 01:34:29,533
So, I mean, as a professional diplomat,

1636
01:34:29,632 --> 01:34:32,800
somebody who's been in this
business all my life, uh,

1637
01:34:32,899 --> 01:34:35,565
I've got to tell you,
that just an awful lot

1638
01:34:35,666 --> 01:34:38,365
of diplomatic rules were broken there.

1639
01:34:38,466 --> 01:34:42,300
NARRATOR: Thieu refused
to accept the terms.

1640
01:34:42,399 --> 01:34:45,565
Allowing North Vietnamese
troops to remain in the South

1641
01:34:45,666 --> 01:34:48,733
would be the death of his country.

1642
01:34:48,832 --> 01:34:53,000
Nonetheless, after Kissinger returned home

1643
01:34:53,100 --> 01:34:55,533
12 days before the election,

1644
01:34:55,632 --> 01:34:59,800
he told the press, "Peace is at hand."

1645
01:34:59,899 --> 01:35:02,365
("Tail Dragger" by Link Wray playing)

1646
01:35:05,466 --> 01:35:08,399
On November 7, 1972,

1647
01:35:08,500 --> 01:35:11,565
Richard Nixon won a stunning victory.

1648
01:35:11,666 --> 01:35:16,399
He was reelected with more
than 60% of the popular vote...

1649
01:35:16,500 --> 01:35:22,399
521 electoral votes to McGovern's 17.

1650
01:35:22,500 --> 01:35:26,199
He took every single state
except Massachusetts

1651
01:35:26,300 --> 01:35:28,800
and the District of Columbia.

1652
01:35:28,899 --> 01:35:32,000
Now, the president resolved to rid himself

1653
01:35:32,100 --> 01:35:37,666
of Vietnam completely before
his second inauguration.

1654
01:35:37,765 --> 01:35:40,533
To calm Thieu's fears of what was to come,

1655
01:35:40,632 --> 01:35:43,466
Nixon launched another massive airlift

1656
01:35:43,565 --> 01:35:46,399
of military equipment to South Vietnam.

1657
01:35:46,500 --> 01:35:49,500
"If we had given this aid
to the North Vietnamese,"

1658
01:35:49,600 --> 01:35:51,399
one American general said,

1659
01:35:51,500 --> 01:35:55,800
"they could have fought us for
the rest of the century."

1660
01:35:55,899 --> 01:35:59,765
The Paris peace talks resumed.

1661
01:35:59,865 --> 01:36:03,132
But then, Le Duc Tho suddenly announced

1662
01:36:03,233 --> 01:36:07,399
he needed to return to
Hanoi for consultation.

1663
01:36:07,500 --> 01:36:09,408
NEGROPONTE: We could only
conclude that maybe they were

1664
01:36:09,432 --> 01:36:10,899
having some doubts about whether

1665
01:36:11,000 --> 01:36:12,899
they wanted to go through
with the agreement,

1666
01:36:13,000 --> 01:36:15,600
because we had sent so many supplies

1667
01:36:15,699 --> 01:36:18,800
to Saigon in the intervening weeks.

1668
01:36:18,899 --> 01:36:21,500
NARRATOR: There turned out to be dissension

1669
01:36:21,600 --> 01:36:24,132
on the communist side as well.

1670
01:36:24,233 --> 01:36:27,699
Hanoi, like Washington, had
not bothered to consult

1671
01:36:27,800 --> 01:36:29,932
with its southern comrades.

1672
01:36:30,033 --> 01:36:32,733
It had dropped the two
demands that meant the most

1673
01:36:32,832 --> 01:36:36,765
to the Viet Cong... the removal
of Thieu, and the release

1674
01:36:36,865 --> 01:36:40,000
of some 30,000 of their prisoners.

1675
01:36:40,100 --> 01:36:43,065
"Hanoi's message was clear,"

1676
01:36:43,166 --> 01:36:45,533
one bitter Viet Cong official said.

1677
01:36:45,632 --> 01:36:49,432
"It cared more about
American prisoners of war

1678
01:36:49,533 --> 01:36:52,199
than it did for us."

1679
01:36:52,300 --> 01:36:55,832
Nixon ordered Kissinger
to suspend the talks,

1680
01:36:55,932 --> 01:36:58,865
and then he resumed the
bombing of North Vietnam

1681
01:36:58,966 --> 01:37:01,132
to further punish Hanoi,

1682
01:37:01,233 --> 01:37:04,065
and to signal to both Hanoi and Saigon

1683
01:37:04,166 --> 01:37:07,733
that the United States
might use its airpower

1684
01:37:07,832 --> 01:37:10,000
to defend South Vietnam

1685
01:37:10,100 --> 01:37:14,500
even after a peace agreement was signed.

1686
01:37:15,899 --> 01:37:17,733
On December 18,

1687
01:37:17,832 --> 01:37:21,199
Nixon unleashed round-the-clock air strikes

1688
01:37:21,300 --> 01:37:24,365
that flattened targets
around Hanoi and Haiphong.

1689
01:37:24,466 --> 01:37:26,199
(explosions)

1690
01:37:26,300 --> 01:37:29,466
It would be remembered as
the Christmas Bombing.

1691
01:37:29,565 --> 01:37:32,899
(bombs exploding, people shouting)

1692
01:37:33,000 --> 01:37:34,765
HAL KUSHNER: And all of a sudden,

1693
01:37:34,865 --> 01:37:36,865
around Christmastime,

1694
01:37:36,966 --> 01:37:39,265
we hear an Arc Light operation,

1695
01:37:39,365 --> 01:37:41,832
B-52s... bom-bom-bom-bom-bom.

1696
01:37:41,932 --> 01:37:43,800
And it's all around, and
it is just exploding.

1697
01:37:43,899 --> 01:37:48,699
And everyone knew they were B-52s.

1698
01:37:48,800 --> 01:37:51,033
And is... in the two
years that I was there,

1699
01:37:51,132 --> 01:37:53,800
that was the first time
I ever heard a bomb.

1700
01:37:53,899 --> 01:37:55,332
And it was close.

1701
01:37:55,432 --> 01:37:57,699
It was really close.

1702
01:37:57,800 --> 01:37:59,932
It was frightening, but
we were still cheering.

1703
01:38:00,033 --> 01:38:03,699
I mean, we were cheering because
something was happening.

1704
01:38:03,800 --> 01:38:06,033
(explosions)

1705
01:38:06,132 --> 01:38:07,932
HUY DUC:

1706
01:38:36,800 --> 01:38:38,166
NARRATOR: Around the world,

1707
01:38:38,265 --> 01:38:41,500
antiwar demonstrators
returned to the streets.

1708
01:38:41,600 --> 01:38:44,699
The prime minister of Sweden
compared the United States

1709
01:38:44,800 --> 01:38:46,432
to Nazi Germany.

1710
01:38:46,533 --> 01:38:48,632
The Pope called the bombing,

1711
01:38:48,733 --> 01:38:51,432
which killed more than 1,600 civilians,

1712
01:38:51,533 --> 01:38:54,632
"the object of daily grief."

1713
01:38:54,733 --> 01:38:59,033
James Reston of theNew York
Times pronounced the raids

1714
01:38:59,132 --> 01:39:00,932
"war by tantrum."

1715
01:39:01,033 --> 01:39:05,466
Republican Senator William
Saxbe of Ohio said

1716
01:39:05,565 --> 01:39:10,166
the president had taken
leave of his senses.

1717
01:39:10,265 --> 01:39:11,800
(gunfire)

1718
01:39:11,899 --> 01:39:15,865
North Vietnam shot down 15 B-52s,

1719
01:39:15,966 --> 01:39:20,233
along with 11 other aircraft.

1720
01:39:20,332 --> 01:39:24,300
93 crewmen were reported missing.

1721
01:39:24,399 --> 01:39:29,065
45 new prisoners of war
were locked up in Hanoi,

1722
01:39:29,166 --> 01:39:33,765
one of whom died in captivity.

1723
01:39:33,865 --> 01:39:38,765
Meanwhile, both the Chinese
and the Soviets pressed Hanoi

1724
01:39:38,865 --> 01:39:41,365
to resume negotiations.

1725
01:39:41,466 --> 01:39:45,065
"The most important thing is
to let the Americans leave,"

1726
01:39:45,166 --> 01:39:48,332
Zhou Enlai told a North
Vietnamese official.

1727
01:39:48,432 --> 01:39:53,132
"The situation will change
in six months or a year."

1728
01:39:55,199 --> 01:39:59,265
On December 26, Hanoi
signaled its willingness

1729
01:39:59,365 --> 01:40:01,600
to return to Paris.

1730
01:40:01,699 --> 01:40:06,265
It would take just six days
to reach a final agreement.

1731
01:40:06,365 --> 01:40:12,565
NEGROPONTE: We bombed them into
accepting our concessions.

1732
01:40:12,666 --> 01:40:16,765
We bombed them into
accepting our concessions.

1733
01:40:16,865 --> 01:40:20,600
And I stand by that statement,
because, in effect,

1734
01:40:20,699 --> 01:40:26,932
what we did was to carry out
this massive bombing campaign

1735
01:40:27,033 --> 01:40:31,832
in order to basically get
back to pretty much exactly

1736
01:40:31,932 --> 01:40:35,565
where we were at the end of October in '72.

1737
01:40:37,533 --> 01:40:40,466
NARRATOR: President Thieu
still balked at signing on.

1738
01:40:40,565 --> 01:40:42,832
Nixon was adamant.

1739
01:40:42,932 --> 01:40:45,932
Thieu had to go along with
what Washington and Hanoi

1740
01:40:46,033 --> 01:40:47,600
had worked out.

1741
01:40:47,699 --> 01:40:50,399
But without informing Congress,

1742
01:40:50,500 --> 01:40:53,399
the president assured Thieu in writing

1743
01:40:53,500 --> 01:40:57,233
that the United States would
"respond with full force"

1744
01:40:57,332 --> 01:41:00,932
if the North ever violated the agreement.

1745
01:41:01,033 --> 01:41:04,565
"The Americans really leave
me no choice," Thieu said.

1746
01:41:04,666 --> 01:41:08,533
"Either sign or they will cut off aid.

1747
01:41:08,632 --> 01:41:12,733
"On the other hand, we have an
absolute guarantee from Nixon

1748
01:41:12,832 --> 01:41:15,033
"to defend the country.

1749
01:41:15,132 --> 01:41:19,600
"I am going to agree to sign
and hold him to his word.

1750
01:41:19,699 --> 01:41:23,399
He is an honest man and I
am going to trust him."

1751
01:41:32,065 --> 01:41:36,132
On January 22, 1973,

1752
01:41:36,233 --> 01:41:40,132
at his ranch in the Hill Country of Texas,

1753
01:41:40,233 --> 01:41:43,166
Lyndon Baines Johnson,

1754
01:41:43,265 --> 01:41:45,865
the president who had
committed the United States

1755
01:41:45,966 --> 01:41:48,832
to a ground war in Vietnam,

1756
01:41:48,932 --> 01:41:53,233
and had seen that war undercut
his domestic social programs

1757
01:41:53,332 --> 01:41:56,332
and end his political career,

1758
01:41:56,432 --> 01:41:58,600
died of congestive heart failure.

1759
01:42:03,832 --> 01:42:08,632
The following evening, Richard
Nixon spoke to the nation.

1760
01:42:08,733 --> 01:42:11,332
28 years after the United States

1761
01:42:11,432 --> 01:42:14,233
first became involved in Vietnam,

1762
01:42:14,332 --> 01:42:17,199
it was finally getting out.

1763
01:42:17,300 --> 01:42:18,733
NIXON: I have asked for this radio

1764
01:42:18,832 --> 01:42:21,100
and television time tonight

1765
01:42:21,199 --> 01:42:24,666
for the purpose of announcing that we today

1766
01:42:24,765 --> 01:42:28,033
have concluded an agreement to end the war

1767
01:42:28,132 --> 01:42:32,132
and bring peace with honor in
Vietnam and in Southeast Asia.

1768
01:42:32,233 --> 01:42:35,632
A cease-fire, internationally supervised,

1769
01:42:35,733 --> 01:42:39,533
will begin at 7:00 p.m.
this Saturday, January 27,

1770
01:42:39,632 --> 01:42:41,365
Washington time.

1771
01:42:41,466 --> 01:42:43,466
